# GitHub Actions — use latest majors

When editing `.github/workflows/**`, pin third-party and official actions to the **current latest major** tag (not deprecated Node 20 runtimes).

## Required versions (update this table when majors bump)

| Action | Tag |
|--------|-----|
| `actions/checkout` | `@v7` |
| `actions/cache` | `@v6` |
| `actions/upload-artifact` | `@v7` |
| `actions/download-artifact` | `@v8` |
| `docker/setup-buildx-action` | `@v4` |
| `docker/login-action` | `@v4` |
| `azure/login` | `@v3` |
| `dorny/paths-filter` | `@v4` |

## Rules

- Use `@v<major>` tags (e.g. `@v7`), not bare `@main` or stale minors on old majors.
- Do **not** use artifact/cache majors that still default to Node 20 (`upload-artifact@v3`, `cache@v4`, etc.).
- Do **not** put `hashFiles()` in workflow-level `env` — it is only valid in job/step expressions.
- Prefer `runs-on: ubuntu-latest` (GitHub-managed runner with current Node runtime for actions).
- For Node.js **application** builds in CI, use the pinned `NODE_IMAGE` from `docker/versions.prod.env` (rendered from `infra/azure/parameters.prod.json`), not `actions/setup-node` with Node 20.

## Example

```yaml
- uses: actions/checkout@v7
- uses: actions/cache@v6
- uses: actions/upload-artifact@v7
- uses: actions/download-artifact@v8
```
